@DATABASE "Game Over"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - G - Game Over"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - G
                   ====================================

                             Game Over Part 1
                             ================


DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Lives   " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(39334,0) ZXAMPoke(38691,0)"}       38691,0:39334,0
     OR
@{"Infinite Lives   " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(39096,0) ZXAMPoke(39345,0)"}       39096,0:39345,0
@{"Infinite Energy  " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(39273,201) ZXAMPoke(38631,201)"}       38631,201
     OR
@{"Infinite Energy  " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(39361,0) ZXAMPoke(39377,0)"}       39361,0:39377,0
@{"Infinite Ammo    " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(32416,0) ZXAMPoke(32378,0)"}       32378,0
@{"Lives = x        " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(48790,255)"}       48790,x (x= 1-255)
@{"Grenades = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(48794,255)"}       48794,x (x= 1-255)
@{"Infinite Grenades" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(32417,0)"}       32417,0

                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).

                         I haven't tested this one as I don't have the
                         game :(

                         The "alternative" POKEs (the OR ones) were by me, as
                         I had hacked this game a while back, and the POKEs
                         were different from the ones in ZXAMPoke.

                         Rastan
@endnode
